"Abstract As of 1 August 1993 a new law on copyright and neighbouring rights became effective in Bulgaria. It was passed by the Parliament on 2 June, but on 16 June some additional amendments had to be voted. The final official text was published in the Official Gazette, issue 56 of 29 June 1993. This law is based on the European copyright system and is most closely linked to the French-Spanish model. It is in compliance with the Berne, Rome and Geneva Conventions and with the latest directives of the EU Council regarding computer programs and neighbouring rights."
